body: Are you using the CUDA execution provider? If so, this fix may be needed: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/2510

No I dont have cuda for now.
I use onnxruntime=1.1.0 which has the "Fix constant folding of node assigned to CUDA" this commit merged already i believe. I tried to build onnxruntime from source. Still the same error. 

I also use optset version 11 when exporting the model to solve the upsampling issue.
What's the input type of the Neg node? Is it int64?
Its float32[1,1,256,256] both input and output of the network .
Are you able to share the model?

The inputs to the Neg nodes in that model are int64, which ORT currently doesn't support (but the ONNX spec says is allowed). The output from Shape is a int64 tensor, and that output goes -> Gather -> Sub -> Div -> Neg, and none of those operations is going to change the type. 

Are there any pytorch export options to avoid using int64 for Neg?
